This is a pnpm monorepo maintaining React and Vue renderers over shared core,
DOM, and style packages.

- Keep framework-neutral behavior in packages/core or packages/dom.
- Preserve equivalent behavior and visual styling across packages/react and
  packages/vue while using framework-native APIs.
- Keep shared component styles in packages/styles rather than duplicating them
  in renderer packages.
- Use the shared contract suites and both playgrounds when changing public
  component behavior.
- Follow the existing TypeScript, React, Vue 3, and Stylus conventions in the
  surrounding code. Vue SFCs use <script setup lang="ts">.
- For linear algebra, use https://github.com/baku89/linearly.
- Write comments and commit messages in English.
- Publish npm packages only through GitHub Actions, never from a local
  environment.
